# Cursor — Global Rules

Before editing any file in this repository, open and read [`PROJECT.md`](../../PROJECT.md). It is the canonical reference for stack, architecture, folder layout, dev commands, and secret handling.

## Cursor-specific behavior

- Treat `PROJECT.md` as authoritative for project facts. Do not paraphrase its decisions back to the user as suggestions; they are already settled.
- Apply path-scoped rules in `.cursor/rules/backend.mdc` (under `Backend/**`) and `.cursor/rules/frontend.mdc` (under `Frontend/**`). When edits cross both, follow the rules of every applicable scope.
- Cursor does not chain imports. If you need detail beyond the inline summaries in the path-scoped rules, open `.agents/instructions/backend.instructions.md` or `.agents/instructions/frontend-ui.instructions.md` directly.

## Universal rules

- Diagnose first; change second. Keep scope tight to the user's task.
- Match existing patterns (feature slices, DTOs, components, tests). Do not introduce parallel architectures.
- Use `decimal` for all money. Preserve transaction discipline and idempotency in lifecycle flows.
- Never modify auth, security, Docker, Caddy, CI/CD, env, or secret configuration without explicit instruction.
- Git safety: no `commit`, `push`, `rebase`, `reset`, or destructive `checkout`. Commit messages go to `COMMIT_MSG.tmp` using Conventional Commits.
- Validate honestly — report what was actually run.
